CP14BaseMagicRune.name: magic rune
CP14BaseMagicRune.description: manifestation of magical energy in the physical plane

CP14BaseMagicImpact.name: magic impact
CP14BaseMagicImpact.description: manifestation of magical energy in the physical plane

CP14BaseSpellScroll.name: spell scroll
CP14BaseSpellScroll.description: A piece of paper with a spell embedded in it. The use of magic destroys the fragile paper, making these scrolls short-lived consumables.

CP14ActionSpellEarthWall.name: Earth wall
CP14ActionSpellEarthWall.description: Raises a solid wall of earth from the bowels.

CP14ActionSpellFlameCreation.name: Flame creation
CP14ActionSpellFlameCreation.description: A artificial flame forms in your hand, illuminating your surroundings. You can throw it to use it as a disposable weapon.

CP14ActionSpellTieflingInnerFire.name: Inner fire
CP14ActionSpellTieflingInnerFire.description: You unleash your inner fire, setting yourself on fire and temporarily speeding up your movement.

CP14ActionSpellFireball.name: Fireball
CP14ActionSpellFireball.description: An effective method of destruction - an explosive fireball

CP14ActionSpellFireRune.name: Fire rune
CP14ActionSpellFireRune.description: You create an area where a scalding stream of fire occurs with little delay.

CP14ActionSpellShadowStep.name: Shadow step
CP14ActionSpellShadowStep.description: A step through the gash of reality that allows you to cover a small of distance quickly

CP14ActionSpellCureBurn.name: Cure burn
CP14ActionSpellCureBurn.description: You heal skin damage caused by excessive cooling or heating.

CP14ActionSpellBloodPurification.name: Blood purification
CP14ActionSpellBloodPurification.description: You cleanse the target's blood of poisons, and restore its volume slightly

CP14ActionSpellCureWounds.name: Cure wounds
CP14ActionSpellCureWounds.description: You heal the target from physical damage

CP14ActionSpellPlantGrowth.name: Plant growth
CP14ActionSpellPlantGrowth.description: You restore health and internal resources to the selected plant.

CP14ActionSpellSphereOfLight.name: Sphere of Light
CP14ActionSpellSphereOfLight.description: Materialization of a bright and safe light source.

CP14SphereOfLight.name: Sphere of light
CP14SphereOfLight.description: A lump of bright light in the shape of a sphere.

CP14ActionSpellFlashLight.name: Flash Light
CP14ActionSpellFlashLight.description: Creates a flash of bright, blinding light.

CP14ActionSpellManaConsume.name: Mana consume
CP14ActionSpellManaConsume.description: You absorb a small amount of mana from the target.

CP14ActionSpellManaConsumeElf.name: Carefull mana consume
CP14ActionSpellManaConsumeElf.description: You absorb a small amount of mana from the target neatly and without loss.

CP14ActionSpellManaGift.name: Mana transfer
CP14ActionSpellManaGift.description: You can transfer a small amount of your magical energy to a target entity or magical object.

CP14ActionSpellShadowGrab.name: Shadow grab
CP14ActionSpellShadowGrab.description: You attract a ghostly hand that draws an object or entity to you

CP14ActionSpellResurrection.name: Resurrection
CP14ActionSpellResurrection.description: You're trying to put the soul back into the body.

CP14ActionSpellSprint.name: Sprint
CP14ActionSpellSprint.description: At the cost of heavy stamina expenditure, you accelerate significantly in movement.

CP14ActionSpellWaterCreation.name: Water creation
CP14ActionSpellWaterCreation.description: Creating a clot of water that is held in a floating balloon shape for some time

CP14ActionSpellBeerCreation.name: Beer creation
CP14ActionSpellBeerCreation.description: A secret spell that materializes beer from pure mana.

CP14ActionSpellIceShards.name: Ice Shards
CP14ActionSpellIceShards.description: Fast ice needles, for rapid shooting of targets.

CP14ClothingBackpackLeather.name: leather backpack
CP14ClothingBackpackLeather.description: You wear this on your back and put items into it.

CP14ClothingBeltQuiver.name: quiver
CP14ClothingBeltQuiver.description: Holds many crossbow bolts, and fits snug around your waist.

CP14ClothingCloakAlchemist.name: alchemist's cloak
CP14ClothingCloakAlchemist.description: An expensive fabric that can withstand acid splashes - the standard for alchemist experts.

CP14ClothingCloakRitualAttireLeather.name: ritual attire with leather
CP14ClothingCloakRitualAttireLeather.description: The traditional attire of Southern mages who have undergone the ritual.

CP14ClothingCloakWhite.name: white cloak
CP14ClothingCloakWhite.description: A spacious white coat. For those who like to look aesthetically pleasing.

CP14ClothingCloakGreen.name: green cloak
CP14ClothingCloakGreen.description: A spacious green coat. For those who like to look aesthetically pleasing.

CP14ClothingCloakBlue.name: blue cloak
CP14ClothingCloakBlue.description: Blue cape covering her entire body.

CP14ClothingCloakGuardBase.name: guard's cloak
CP14ClothingCloakGuardBase.description: Shoulder cape in the standard Imperial Guard colors

CP14ClothingCloakGuardCommander.name: armored cloak of a guard commander
CP14ClothingCloakGuardCommander.description: It is an extremely durable and lightweight cape, custom designed for Imperial Guard commanders

CP14ClothingEyesAlchemyGlasses.name: alchemy glasses
CP14ClothingEyesAlchemyGlasses.description: Special magic infused glasses that allow you to clearly see the composition of any mixtures.

CP14ClothingEyesAlchemyMonocle.name: alchemy monocle
CP14ClothingEyesAlchemyMonocle.description: Special magic infused monocle that allow you to clearly see the composition of any mixtures.

CP14ClothingEyesThaumaturgyGlasses.name: thaumaturgy glasses
CP14ClothingEyesThaumaturgyGlasses.description: Goggles that allow you to scan magical items and creatures to clearly see the amount of energy left in them.

CP14ClothingHeadCapellina.name: capellina
CP14ClothingHeadCapellina.description: Protects against large object strikes to the head.

CP14ClothingHeadWreath.name: floral wreath
CP14ClothingHeadWreath.description: A simple flower decoration. That's so sweet.

CP14ClothingHeadAlchemistBandana.name: alchemist's bandana
CP14ClothingHeadAlchemistBandana.description: Hides your hair from chemical fumes

CP14ClothingHeadBowler.name: bowler hat
CP14ClothingHeadBowler.description: It has an aristocratic air about it...

CP14ClothingHeadBowlerGolden.name: golden bowler hat
CP14ClothingHeadBowlerGolden.description: What an exquisite hat. It's clearly a hat that only sophisticated people prefer to wear.

CP14ClothingHeadCaptainCap.name: captain's cap
CP14ClothingHeadCaptainCap.description: No, look how handsome he is!

CP14ClothingHeadBeretMercenary.name: mercenary beret
CP14ClothingHeadBeretMercenary.description: A large red wool hat decorated with a feather.

CP14ClothingHeadMetalHeadband.name: metall headband
CP14ClothingHeadMetalHeadband.description: The odds of it protecting you from a head shot are slim to none.

CP14ClothingHeadTriangularHat.name: triangular hat
CP14ClothingHeadTriangularHat.description: a big, pointy hat for those who like to look smart.

CP14ClothingHeadTriangularHatGolden.name: golden triangular hat
CP14ClothingHeadTriangularHatGolden.description: a big, pointy hat for those who like to look smart. Decorated with a gold hoop.

CP14ClothingHeadChristmasHat.name: christmas hat
CP14ClothingHeadChristmasHat.description: A festive red hat, nobody remembers why it is customary to wear it.

CP14ClothingMaskSinner.name: Sinner's Mask
CP14ClothingMaskSinner.description: A mask intented to be worn by not the brightest individuals. Executioners put them on themselves and the victim before execution.

CP14ClothingMaskSteelMask.name: steel mask
CP14ClothingMaskSteelMask.description: A steel mask that protects the face from the external effects of iron.

CP14ClothingOuterClothingCopperArmor.name: copper armor
CP14ClothingOuterClothingCopperArmor.description: Quality copper armour, has good protection and is not too heavy.

CP14ClothingOuterClothingCuirass.name: cuirass
CP14ClothingOuterClothingCuirass.description: Light armour plate on the chest, little protection, little heaviness.

CP14ClothingOuterClothingInfantryCuirass.name: infantry cuirass
CP14ClothingOuterClothingInfantryCuirass.description: The light infantry cuirass, unlike the original, also protects from the back.

CP14ClothingOuterClothingCuirassLoinclot.name: cuirass loincloth
CP14ClothingOuterClothingCuirassLoinclot.description: A heavier version of the cuirass, covering only the top of the legs.

CP14ClothingOuterClothingCuirassLeg.name: cuirass leg
CP14ClothingOuterClothingCuirassLeg.description: A heavier cuirass that completely covers the legs.

CP14ClothingPantsBase.description: Pants to cover my thighs from the cold.

CP14ClothingPantsAristocratic.name: aristocrat's pants
CP14ClothingPantsAristocratic.description: Pants with enough quality fabric that you don't want to cave in them.

CP14ClothingPantsSouthernMagician.name: southern magician's dress
CP14ClothingPantsSouthernMagician.description: A traditional southern mage skirt, rather loose.

CP14ClothingPantsGuardsChainmailSkirt.name: guard's chainmail skirt
CP14ClothingPantsGuardsChainmailSkirt.description: Skirt with stitched clutch padding, in standard Imperial Guard uniform colors.

CP14ClothingRingIceShards.name: ice shards conductive ring
CP14ClothingRingIceShards.description: A standard mana-conductive ring that allows the user to summon ice shards.

CP14ClothingRingFireball.name: fireball conductive ring
CP14ClothingRingFireball.description: A standard mana-conductive ring that allows the user to summon fireballs.

CP14ClothingRingFlashLight.name: flash conductive ring
CP14ClothingRingFlashLight.description: A standard mana-conductive ring that allows the user to create a bright flash of light that blinds enemies.

CP14ClothingShirtBase.description: Pleasant to the touch material, in a comfortable loose shirt shape.

CP14ClothingShirtBanker.name: banker's shirt
CP14ClothingShirtBanker.description: A white shirt with bronze inserts. Standard bank employee costume.

CP14ClothingShirtYellowWizard.name: yellow wizard shirt
CP14ClothingShirtYellowWizard.description: A loose magician's shirt, comfortable and nice looking.

CP14ClothingShirtGuardBase.name: guard's chainmail shirt
CP14ClothingShirtGuardBase.description: Skirt with stitched clutch padding, in standard Imperial Guard uniform colors.

CP14ClothingShoesBlack.name: simple black boots
CP14ClothingShoesBlack.description: They won't hold moisture, but it's better than going barefoot.

CP14ClothingShoesAristocraticBlack.name: aristocratic black boots
CP14ClothingShoesAristocraticBlack.description: They're expensive enough that you don't want to go caving in them.

CP14ClothingShoesSandals.name: sandals
CP14ClothingShoesSandals.description: Sandals made of rough leather and metal fastenings

CP14BankStorageMarker.name: Bank vault marker
CP14BankStorageMarker.description: Marks the specified area as a “bank vault” to credit all bankers with treasure storage goals

CP14TravelingStoreshipAnchor.name: traveling storeship anchor
CP14TravelingStoreshipAnchor.description: the point of adhesion of a traveling storeship to the surface. Keep your eyes to the sky so you don't get crushed!

CP14VentCritterMarker.name: Mob spawners marker
CP14VentCritterMarker.description: random creatures breaking out of the demiplanes will spawn at this location

CP14BaseMobGroupSpawner.name: pulsating demiplane rift
CP14BaseMobGroupSpawner.description: Something from the demiplanes is bursting into your world! Look out!

CP14MobRabbit.name: rabbit
CP14MobRabbit.description: A little fluffy rabbit. I could eat it.

CP14MobPig.name: pig
CP14MobPig.description: An omnivorous and unpretentious animal that is sure to make juicy cuts of meat.

CP14MobBoar.name: boar
CP14MobBoar.description: A distant relative of pigs, same pros, but unlike its peaceful relatives, will definitely try to pick you up on its fangs if you show aggression towards it.

CP14MobDinoYumkaraptor.name: yumkaraptor
CP14MobDinoYumkaraptor.description: A large scaly lizard, an obvious predator that liked to snack on meat.

CP14MobDinoSmallHydra.name: small hydra
CP14MobDinoSmallHydra.description: The small two-headed lizard, despite its size, can be quite dangerous.

CP14MobMonsterMole.name: predatory mole
CP14MobMonsterMole.description: Hunts in the dark and loves the taste of meat and blood in its mouth.

CP14ActionMoleSpellSubterraneanLeap.name: Subterranean leap
CP14ActionMoleSpellSubterraneanLeap.description: Make a subterranean leap, quickly approaching the victim.

CP14MobUndeadSkeleton.name: skeleton
CP14MobUndeadSkeleton.description: animated by the dark magic of a fragile skeleton. Skeletons are usually extremely intelligent creatures, controlled by a recently deceased soul.

CP14MobUndeadZombie.name: walking dead
CP14MobUndeadZombie.description: A reanimated rotting body of a dead man wanting to devour the living.

CP14RitualGrimoire.name: ritualist's grimoire
CP14RitualGrimoire.description: a book that holds the knowledge of hundreds of ritualists before you. Use it on an active ritual to get all the information about its current state.

CP14PaperFolderBase.name: folder
CP14PaperFolderBase.description: A folder filled with some paperwork.

CP14BookKnowledgeBase.name: knowledge book
CP14BookKnowledgeBase.description: This book holds valuable knowledge that you can learn... if you're ready for it.

CP14PenFeather.name: fountain pen
CP14PenFeather.description: A sharp clipped feather of a bird, adapted as a writing implement.

CP14Inkwell.name: inkwell
CP14Inkwell.description: An endless (for now) source of ink for your letters

CP14StampBase.name: generic rubber stamp
CP14StampBase.description: A rubber stamp for stamping important documents.

CP14GreenBottle.name: green Bottle
CP14GreenBottle.description: A green bottle perfect for drinking beer.

CP14BlueBottle.name: blue bottle
CP14BlueBottle.description: A blue vial perfect for drinking whiskey.

CP14RedBottle.name: red Bottle
CP14RedBottle.description: A red bottle perfect for drinking wine.

CP14FoodCheeseWheel.name: cheese wheel
CP14FoodCheeseWheel.description: A large wheel of soft, fragrant piece of cheese.

CP14FoodCheesePart.name: cheese
CP14FoodCheesePart.description: A triangle of soft, fragrant cheese.

CP14FoodCheeseSlice.name: cheese slice
CP14FoodCheeseSlice.description: A thin slice of delicious smelling cheese.

CP14FoodDoughLarge.name: large piece of dough
CP14FoodDoughLarge.description: The perfect ingredient for any flour product. The only thing left to do is to shape it.

CP14FoodMeatLambCutlet.name: lamb cutlet
CP14FoodMeatLambCutlet.description: the result of mixing sliced lamb and egg - a raw round cutlet.

CP14BasePlate.description: This is your plate for a delicious meal!

CP14FoodTomatoesSlice.name: tomato slice
CP14FoodTomatoesSlice.description: Thin red tomato slice. It's no longer as nice to throw at people as whole tomatoes.

CP14SilverCoin.name: silver coin
CP14SilverCoin.description: A valuable coin made from a precisely calibrated silver alloy..... and something else. Equal in value to ten coppers.

CP14GoldCoin.name: gold coin
CP14GoldCoin.description: A gold, big, beautiful coin. Valuable enough to be stolen by bandits. Equal in value to ten silver coins.

CP14PlatinumCoin.name: platinum coin
CP14PlatinumCoin.description: A platinum coin? It's so rare. Ten gold pieces is the price of one.

CP14JewelryRuby.name: ruby
CP14JewelryRuby.description: A beautiful ruby stone that's worth a lot of money.

CP14JewelryEmerald.name: emerald
CP14JewelryEmerald.description: A beautiful emerald stone that's worth a lot of money.

CP14JewelrySapphire.name: sapphire
CP14JewelrySapphire.description: A beautiful sapphire stone that's worth a lot of money.

CP14JewelryTopaz.name: topaz
CP14JewelryTopaz.description: A beautiful topaz stone that's worth a lot of money.

CP14Wallet.name: wallet
CP14Wallet.description: A small wallet, handy for storing coins.

CP14Wheat.name: wheat bushel
CP14Wheat.description: You have the choice of either planting the grains again or grinding them into flour.

CP14BloodFlower.name: blood rose
CP14BloodFlower.description: Scarlet flowers growing where blood has been spilled.

CP14AgaricMushroom.name: fly agaric
CP14AgaricMushroom.description: This poisonous mushroom can often be found near bodies of water or other wet areas. It is not recommended for consumption.

CP14ChromiumSlime.name: chromium slime
CP14ChromiumSlime.description: This rare thick substance can be found in a stream of water as if it has a mind of its own. When trying to change the slime itself - the slime changes the reagent it interacts with.

CP14WildSage.name: wild sage root
CP14WildSage.description: Root of a ubiquitous medicinal plant, not bad at healing physical injuries, and inducing coughing.

CP14QuartzShard.name: rough quartz
CP14QuartzShard.description: a natural crystal that is a natural storage of magical energy. Its color reflects the quality of the crystal - the higher the emission spectrum, the higher the level of energy leakage.

CP14LumiMushroom.name: lumishroom
CP14LumiMushroom.description: A faintly luminous mushroom. Often used by alchemists as a means of concentrating solutions.

CP14BlueAmanita.name: blue Amanita
CP14BlueAmanita.description: A sky blue flower known for its medicinal and magical properties.

CP14Dayflin.name: yellow dayflin
CP14Dayflin.description: A yellow sun flower that smells like melted milk. Can be processed into a yellow dye.

CP14AirLily.name: air lily
CP14AirLily.description: A light, delicate and airy flower. It is said that its special properties even allow it to breathe underwater...

CP14FluteInstrument.name: flute
CP14FluteInstrument.description: A compact musical wind instrument, popular in villages as well as with large musical troupes.

CP14LyraInstrument.name: lyra
CP14LyraInstrument.description: A common stringed instrument throughout Sylate, popular with various bards and musical troupes.

CP14BaseKey.name: key
CP14BaseKey.description: A small, intricate piece of metal that opens some locks. Don't give it to anyone!

CP14BaseLockpick.name: lockpick
CP14BaseLockpick.description: A thief's tool that, with proper skill and skill, allows you to pick any lock.

CP14BaseKeyRing.name: key ring
CP14BaseKeyRing.description: Allows you to comfortably store a large number of keys in one place.

CP14KeyPersonalHouseAbstractLoadoutDummy.name: a key to a random personal home (limited per map)

CP14Ash1.name: ash
CP14Ash1.description: It used to be something that could be interesting and useful, now it's not.

CP14CopperBar1.name: copper bar
CP14CopperBar1.description: A heavy, slightly green, piece of refined copper

CP14IronBar1.name: iron bar
CP14IronBar1.description: A heavy piece of refined iron

CP14GoldBar1.name: gold bar
CP14GoldBar1.description: A warm to the touch, soft piece of refined gold.

CP14GlassSheet1.name: glass sheet
CP14GlassSheet1.description: Treated quartz glass, transmits light well, and is nice to look at!

CP14MithrilBar1.name: mithril bar
CP14MithrilBar1.description: A warm to the touch, soft piece of refined mithril.

CP14BaseDye.name: dye
CP14BaseDye.description: A bright, colorful dye used to paint various things.

CP14OreCopper.name: copper ore
CP14OreCopper.description: A piece of pale, heavy copper.

CP14OreIron.name: iron ore
CP14OreIron.description: A piece of cold, heavy iron.

CP14OreGold.name: gold ore
CP14OreGold.description: A piece of soft, pure gold.

CP14OreMithril.name: mithril ore
CP14OreMithril.description: A piece of enchanted, pure mithril.

CP14ScrapCopper.name: copper scrap
CP14ScrapCopper.description: Crooked pieces of copper. Useless. Only to be melted down.

CP14ScrapIron.name: iron scrap
CP14ScrapIron.description: Crooked pieces of iron. Useless. Only to be melted down.

CP14ScrapGold.name: golden scrap
CP14ScrapGold.description: Crooked pieces of gold. Useless. Only to be melted down.

CP14ScrapMithril.name: mithril scrap
CP14ScrapMithril.description: Crooked pieces of mithril. Useless. Only to be melted down.

CP14DirtBlock1.name: dirt block
CP14DirtBlock1.description: A block of excellent black soil.

CP14WoodLog.name: wooden log
CP14WoodLog.description: A piece of unprocessed wood. Good material for building, or starting a fire.

CP14Nail1.name: nails
CP14Nail1.description: A basic carpenter's tool that allows you to do unimaginable things with wood.

CP14FloraMaterial1.name: flora material
CP14FloraMaterial1.description: An organic material used for medicinal or construction purposes.

CP14String.name: strings
CP14String.description: Thin thread. Material for mending clothes, or sewing new ones.

CP14Candle.name: candle
CP14Candle.description: A thin wick threaded through fat.

CP14CandleInfinite.name: magic candle
CP14CandleInfinite.description: A magically created candle that never goes out, the flame seems cold and dead, but still burning.

CP14ModularGripLong.description: A tool for your purposes! Now long enough to hold in two hands.

CP14ModularBladeAxeBase.description: A axe blade without a hilt. A blacksmith can use it as a spare part to create a weapon.

CP14ModularBladeDaggerBase.description: A dagger blade without a hilt. A blacksmith can use it as a spare part to create a weapon.

CP14ModularBladeMaceBase.description: A mace ball without a hilt. A blacksmith can use it as a spare part to create a weapon.

CP14ModularBladePickaxeBase.description: A pickaxe head without a hilt. A blacksmith can use it as a spare part to create a tool.

CP14ModularBladeRapierBase.description: A rapier blade without a hilt. A blacksmith can use it as a spare part to create a weapon.

CP14ModularBladeShovelBase.description: A shovel blade without a hilt. A blacksmith can use it as a spare part to create a tool.

CP14ModularBladeSickleBase.description: A sickle blade without a hilt. A blacksmith can use it as a spare part to create a weapon.

CP14ModularBladeSpearBase.description: Hiltless spearhead. A blacksmith can use it as a spare part to create a weapon.

CP14ModularBladeSwordBase.description: A sword blade without a hilt. A blacksmith can use it as a spare part to create a weapon.

CP14Cauldron.name: cauldron
CP14Cauldron.description: A heavy cauldron. It is not as bulky as a vat, but can be carried in your hands.

CP14Pestle.name: pestle
CP14Pestle.description: A device for conveniently grinding various materials into liquid

CP14Mortar.name: mortar
CP14Mortar.description: Alchemical sturdy plate for grinding reagents

CP14Dropper.name: dropper
CP14Dropper.description: Small dropper for managing very small values of liquids

CP14Syringe.name: syringe
CP14Syringe.description: Used to draw blood samples from mobs, or to inject them with reagents.

CP14VialTiny.name: tiny vial
CP14VialTiny.description: A fragile glass vial to hold a tiny amount of liquid.

CP14VialTinyReinforced.name: reinforced tiny vial
CP14VialTinyReinforced.description: A reinforced glass vial to hold a tiny amount of liquid.

CP14VialSmall.name: small vial
CP14VialSmall.description: A fragile glass vial to hold a small amount of liquid.

CP14VialSmallReinforced.name: reinforced small vial
CP14VialSmallReinforced.description: A reinforced glass vial to hold a small amount of liquid.

CP14SeedWheat.name: wheat seeds
CP14SeedWheat.description: Small wheat seeds. What will you do with them? Grind them into flour, or plant them again?

CP14SeedPumpkin.name: pumpkin seeds
CP14SeedPumpkin.description: Pumpkin seeds. Some pumpkin seems to have been gutted and butchered.

CP14SeedCucumber.name: cucumber seeds
CP14SeedCucumber.description: Are cucumber seeds. You know what to do with them.

CP14SeedTomato.name: tomato seeds
CP14SeedTomato.description: It looks like powder! They're so small, these seeds.

CP14HerbalBandage.name: herbal bandage
CP14HerbalBandage.description: A bandage net woven from grass, not the most reliable or useful thing, but better than nothing.

CP14Gauze.name: gauze
CP14Gauze.description: Dense cloth gauze, to prevent valuable blood from leaking out of the body.

CP14EnergyCrystalBase.description: A crystal shard capable of storing magical energy.

CP14RitualChalk.name: ritual chalk
CP14RitualChalk.description: Quartz chalk, handy for drawing temporary ritual circles.

CP14BaseSubdimensionalKey.name: demiplane key
CP14BaseSubdimensionalKey.description: The core that connects the real world to the demiplane. Use it to open a temporary passage to the other world.

CP14Lighter.name: flint and steel
CP14Lighter.description: Setting things on fire. Absolutely, 100% not from minecraft.

CP14Rope.name: rope
CP14Rope.description: Multifunctional rope. You can tie something with it. Or someone.

CP14Scissors.name: scissors
CP14Scissors.description: A tool for shredding wool, hair, clothing, and, if not handled carefully, even fingers.

CP14BaseSharpeningStone.name: sharpening stone
CP14BaseSharpeningStone.description: Allows you to sharpen blunted weapons. If you overdo it, you may well sharpen the weapon completely.

CP14Torch.name: torch
CP14Torch.description: At its core, a stick burning on one side. Used to light up the area.

CP14BaseWallpaper.description: Thin paper wallpaper. You can glue them on the walls from different sides, or peel them off with any sharp object.

CP14ModularIronAxe.name: iron axe
CP14ModularIronAxe.description: A heavy axe for cutting firewood or heads.

CP14ModularIronDagger.name: iron dagger
CP14ModularIronDagger.description: A small, multi-purpose, sharp blade. You can cut meat or throw it at a goblin.

CP14ModularIronMace.name: iron mace
CP14ModularIronMace.description: A heavy piece of metal on a long stick. What could be simpler than that?

CP14ModularIronPickaxe.name: iron pickaxe
CP14ModularIronPickaxe.description: Notched to perfection, for jamming it into rocks

CP14ModularIronShovel.name: iron shovel
CP14ModularIronShovel.description: An implement for digging up earth, digging beds or graves.

CP14ModularIronSickle.name: iron sickle
CP14ModularIronSickle.description: Originally developed as a weapon against grass, the sickle suddenly proved itself good at the bloodier harvest as well.

CP14ModularIronSpear.name: iron spear
CP14ModularIronSpear.description: The spear is a weapon whose effectiveness has stood the test of time.

CP14ModularIronKunai.name: iron kunai
CP14ModularIronKunai.description: An effective throwing weapon. Throw it at a wall, or no, better yet, at a goblin!

CP14ModularIronSword.name: iron sword
CP14ModularIronSword.description: the gold standard of edged weapons. Medium length, comfortable grip. No frills.

CP14ModularGuardHalberd.name: guard's halberd
CP14ModularGuardHalberd.description: The standard issue armament of the imperial guard. A long iron halberd adorned with blue feathers and brass

CP14BaseLightCrossbow.name: light crossbow
CP14BaseLightCrossbow.description: A small, compact crossbow that is comfortable to hold with one hand. Not too accurate on the reverse side.

CP14Crossbolt.name: crossbow bolt
CP14Crossbolt.description: Rod with a sharpened spike. No plumage, they're not bows.

CP14_NeutralCluster_Root.name: Te-Se-Ra
CP14_NeutralCluster_Root.description: The perfect energetic position to begin any ritual.

CP14Chasm.name: chasm
CP14Chasm.description: You can't even see the bottom.

CP14CrystalBase.name: sparkling quartz
CP14CrystalBase.description: bioluminescent quartz crystals that can take on any color - a very handy light source in a deep caves. Unfortunately, the luminous properties are very hard to preserve.

CP14LaddersDownBase.name: stairway down
CP14LaddersDownBase.description: The dark depths of the underworld are calling you.

CP14LaddersUpBase.name: stairway up
CP14LaddersUpBase.description: A way out of the dark underworld into the overworld.

CP14DemiplaneLinkCrystal.name: demiplane link crystal
CP14DemiplaneLinkCrystal.description: Maintains communication with the demiplanes while charged. Causes mosnters from the demiplanes to attack the city. Once it is discharged, the game is over.

CP14TravelingShop.name: city trading information board
CP14TravelingShop.description: Allows you to track what the city is selling and buying right now.

CP14DPSMeter.name: DPS Meter
CP14DPSMeter.description: Counts the average damage per second. If you stop hitting it, it shows the result.

CP14DemiplanRiftCore.name: demiplan rift core
CP14DemiplanRiftCore.description: A subtle connection between the real world and the demiplane where the adventurers went. Sooner or later they will return from there.

CP14DemiplaneTimedRadiusPassway.name: pulsating demiplane rift
CP14DemiplaneTimedRadiusPassway.description: This rift is gaining strength, and will trap all nearby creatures in a demiplane in a second!

CP14DemiplanePassway.name: demiplane rift
CP14DemiplanePassway.description: A gap in space that allows you to travel between world and demiplanes.

CP14WallmountFlagAlchemist.name: alchemist tapestry
CP14WallmountFlagAlchemist.description: A tapestry with a potion symbol, indicating that alchemists dwell here.

CP14WallmountFlagBlacksmith.name: blacksmith tapestry
CP14WallmountFlagBlacksmith.description: A tapestry with a anvil symbol, indicating that blacksmiths dwell here.

CP14WallmountFlagTavern.name: tavern tapestry
CP14WallmountFlagTavern.description: A tapestry with a beer symbol, indicating that tavern is here.

CP14WallmountFlagBank.name: bank tapestry
CP14WallmountFlagBank.description: A tapestry with a coins symbol indicating that this is where the bankers live.

CP14WallmountFlagBankVault.name: bank vault tapestry
CP14WallmountFlagBankVault.description: A tapestry with a vault symbol indicating that this is where the bank vaults reside.

CP14WallmountFlagBankCrates.name: bank crates tapestry
CP14WallmountFlagBankCrates.description: A tapestry with a crates symbol indicating that this is where the bank vaults reside.

CP14WallmountFlagBankShip.name: bank ship tapestry
CP14WallmountFlagBankShip.description: A tapestry with a ship symbol denoting that there is a ship here to trade with the city.

CP14WallmountFlagBankCommandant.name: commandant tapestry
CP14WallmountFlagBankCommandant.description: A tapestry with a star symbol indicating that the commandant lives here.

CP14WallmountFlagGuardSwords.name: guard tapestry
CP14WallmountFlagGuardSwords.description: A tapestry with a swords symbol denoting that the guards are here.

CP14WallmountFlagGuardShield.name: guard tapestry
CP14WallmountFlagGuardShield.description: A tapestry with a shield symbol denoting that the guards are here.

CP14WallmountFlagGuardCommander.name: guard commander tapestry
CP14WallmountFlagGuardCommander.description: A tapestry with a star symbol indicating that the Guard Commandant lives here.

CP14WallmountPaintingCandle.name: candle painting
CP14WallmountPaintingCandle.description: A nicely drawn candle in a frame.

CP14WallmountPaintingWoman.name: painting of a woman
CP14WallmountPaintingWoman.description: The painting depicts a woman with a mysterious smile.

CP14WallmountPaintingSaint.name: painting of a saint
CP14WallmountPaintingSaint.description: A drawing of a nun with a halo over her head. This is how you can feel the holiness of the picture.

CP14StatueAngel.name: angel statue
CP14StatueAngel.description: A divine statue of a praying angel.

CP14BaseTombstone.name: tombstone
CP14BaseTombstone.description: A piece of stone placed in memory of the dead.

CP14Cliff.name: cliff
CP14Cliff.description: Severe unevenness of the natural landscape.

CP14FloorWater.name: water
CP14FloorWater.description: A trough of plain water. Clean enough for consumption

CP14HighBush.name: high bush
CP14HighBush.description: Very tall and dense thickets. Perhaps someone is watching you from them

CP14BaseRock.name: rock
CP14BaseRock.description: A piece of rock. Hard, heavy, useless.

CP14RoyalPumpkin.name: royal pumpkin
CP14RoyalPumpkin.description: It's a huge pumpkin, it feels like you could even make a carriage out of it.

CP14Snowdrift.name: snowdrift
CP14Snowdrift.description: A big, cold pile of snow.

CP14BaseTree.name: tree
CP14BaseTree.description: Decades of life and growth, saturating the surrounding nature with fresh air.

CP14WaterLilies.name: water lilies
CP14WaterLilies.description: Wow, these are plants that don't grow on land, but on water! Nature is amazing.

CP14WaterReeds.name: reed
CP14WaterReeds.description: Usually grows in swamps and on river banks.

CP14GatherableBloodFlower.name: blood rose
CP14GatherableBloodFlower.description: Scarlet flowers growing where blood has been spilled.

CP14GatherableDayflin.name: yellow dayflin
CP14GatherableDayflin.description: A yellow sun flower that smells like melted milk. Can be processed into a yellow dye.

CP14GatherableFlyAgaric.name: fly agaric
CP14GatherableFlyAgaric.description: This poisonous mushroom can often be found near bodies of water or other wet areas. It is not recommended for consumption.

CP14GatherableChromiumSlime.name: chromium slime
CP14GatherableChromiumSlime.description: This rare thick substance can be found in a stream of water as if it has a mind of its own. When trying to change the slime itself - the slime changes the reagent it interacts with.

CP14GatherableWildSage.name: wild sage
CP14GatherableWildSage.description: Root of this ubiquitous medicinal plant not bad at healing physical injuries, and inducing coughing.

CP14GatherableLumiMushroom.name: lumishroom
CP14GatherableLumiMushroom.description: A faintly luminous mushroom. Often used by alchemists as a means of concentrating solutions.

CP14QuartzCrystal.name: quartz
CP14QuartzCrystal.description: Quartz is an essential mineral capable of interacting with magical energy. It is highly sought after by alchemists for extracting beneficial properties from liquids

CP14GatherableBlueAmanita.name: blue Amanita
CP14GatherableBlueAmanita.description: A sky blue flower known for its medicinal and magical properties.

CP14PlantCabbageDeath.name: dead cabbage
CP14PlantCabbageDeath.description: The sad spectacle of wasted food.

CP14PlantCucumberDeath.name: dead cucumber
CP14PlantCucumberDeath.description: The sad spectacle of wasted food.

CP14PlantPotatoDeath.name: dead potato
CP14PlantPotatoDeath.description: The sad spectacle of wasted food.

CP14PlantPumpkinDeath.name: dead pumpkin
CP14PlantPumpkinDeath.description: The sad spectacle of wasted food.

CP14PlantTomatoesDeath.name: dead tomatoes
CP14PlantTomatoesDeath.description: The sad spectacle of wasted food.

CP14PlantWheat.name: wheat
CP14PlantWheat.description: Most popular crop. Unpretentious, it opens the way to an abundance of flour products.

CP14PlantWheatDeath.name: dead wheat
CP14PlantWheatDeath.description: The sad spectacle of wasted food.

CP14Bonfire.name: bonfire
CP14Bonfire.description: A pile of logs stacked together, ready to burst into flames at the slightest spark.

C14IronCabinet.name: iron cabinet
C14IronCabinet.description: an iron cabinet. Sturdy, lockable. You can store your valuables here without fear of some burglar taking it all for himself.

C14IronCabinetCargo.name: trade box
C14IronCabinetCargo.description: An armored vault for storing money for trade with the city. City workers will unload their earnings here, or take them from here when you want to buy something.

CP14Lamppost.name: lamppost
CP14Lamppost.description: A lantern hanging from a pole.

CP14LamppostBlue.name: lamppost
CP14LamppostBlue.description: A lantern hanging from a pole.

CP14TableWooden.name: wooden table
CP14TableWooden.description: A simple table made of boards.

CP14TableWoodenRound.name: round wooden table
CP14TableWoodenRound.description: A simple table made of boards.

CP14WallmountTorch.name: wallmount torch
CP14WallmountTorch.description: A good, reliable light source. Too bad it doesn't last.

CP14WallmountBarShelfA.name: bar shelf
CP14WallmountBarShelfA.description: Wall shelves to store your wine collection

CP14BaseRoof.name: roof
CP14BaseRoof.description: A roof over your head to protect you from the heat of the sun or the weather.

CP14ShuttleWingBase.name: airship wing
CP14ShuttleWingBase.description: Giant webbed wings, capable, along with magic, of holding the heaviest objects in the air.

CP14AlchemyFurnace.name: alchemy furnace
CP14AlchemyFurnace.description: A furnace fueled by wood, coal, or any other burning material. Handy for heating your alchemical potions.

CP14BaseSharpeningStoneStructure.name: stationary sharpening stone
CP14BaseSharpeningStoneStructure.description: A strong, durable sharpening stone capable of sharpening weapons without much damage to them.

CP14CashConverter.name: cash converter
CP14CashConverter.description: A simple magical device connected by small portals to the empire's central bank. It allows you to convert coins between denominations, and doesn't even charge interest! That's generous.

CP14SeedbedWooden.name: seedbed
CP14SeedbedWooden.description: A wooden tub with a pile of earth adapted for growing plants.

CP14CrateDirtPitGrave.name: dirt pit
CP14CrateDirtPitGrave.description: There's something buried here... or someone...

CP14WallStone.name: rock
CP14WallStone.description: A solid stone natural wall. It has a cave-like coldness to it.

CP14WallStoneIndestructable.name: dense rock
CP14WallStoneIndestructable.description: An extremely durable stone. Your tools don't seem to be enough to break through it.

CP14WallDirt.name: earth wall
CP14WallDirt.description: A tall pile of dirt. Can a house be built from it?

CP14WallSnow.name: snow wall
CP14WallSnow.description: A tall pile of snow. Can a house be built from it?

CP14WallStoneCopperOre.description: A solid stone natural wall. You can see the sharp flecks of copper in it.

CP14WallStoneIronOre.description: A solid stone natural wall. You can see the sharp flecks of iron in it.

CP14WallStoneGoldOre.description: A solid stone natural wall. You see the tantalizing particles of gold in it.

CP14WallStoneMithrilOre.description: A solid stone natural wall. You see the tantalizing particles of mithril in it.

CP14BaseWall.name: wall
CP14BaseWall.description: Sturdy enough to cover you from threats or cold winds.

CP14WindowDirectional.name: directional window
CP14WindowDirectional.description: Don't smudge up the glass down there.

CP14WindowStoneBrick.name: stone brick window
CP14WindowStoneBrick.description: A stone brick wall with a glass window in it.

CP14WindowMarbleBrick.name: marble brick window
CP14WindowMarbleBrick.description: A stone brick wall with a glass window in it.

CP14FlameCreationArtificialFlame.name: artificial flame
CP14FlameCreationArtificialFlame.description: A magically created artificial flame burning directly into the air. Not a bad light source, or a weapon if you throw it in someone's face.

CP14LiquidDropWater.name: floating liquid drop
CP14LiquidDropWater.description: A clot of liquid held in the shape of a ball by magic

CP14ClothingCloakBlacksmithArpon.name: blacksmith's apron
CP14ClothingCloakBlacksmithArpon.description: Loose leather strips, still actually being clothing.

CP14ClothingCloakMaidArpon.name: maid's apron
CP14ClothingCloakMaidArpon.description: Cleanliness, orderliness and obedience are the main traits of a good maid.

CP14ClothingCloakCommandantJacket.name: commandant's jacket
CP14ClothingCloakCommandantJacket.description: the colors white and gold tell you that you're looking at a higher power.

CP14ClothingCloakCaptainJacket.name: captain's jacket
CP14ClothingCloakCaptainJacket.description: the colors white and gold tell you that you're looking at a higher power.

CP14MobMonsterMosquito.name: bloodworm mosquitoes
CP14MobMonsterMosquito.description: A bloodthirsty swarm of small mosquitoes just waiting for a soft flesh for a bloody feast.

CP14FoodTomatoes.name: tomatoes
CP14FoodTomatoes.description: A red, juicy tomato. You just want to throw it in someone's face!

CP14Snowball.name: snowball
CP14Snowball.description: A small handful of snow, handy for throwing.

CP14ManaOperationGlove.name: mana glove
CP14ManaOperationGlove.description: An unsophisticated but aesthetically pleasing blend of technology and magic crystals that allows you to operate with raw mana: siphoning it from some objects and pumping it into others.

CP14CrystalLamp.name: crystal lamp
CP14CrystalLamp.description: A device that converts energy from crystals into a source of directional light.  Convenient for traveling

CP14MagicHealingStaff.name: magic healing staff
CP14MagicHealingStaff.description: A long, half-tech, half-magic stick designed to convert magical energy into healing spells.

CP14BaseBattleHammer.name: battle hammer
CP14BaseBattleHammer.description: A big heavy hammer. You better not get in his way!

CP14BaseLightHammer.name: light hammer
CP14BaseLightHammer.description: A small hammer. Good for carpentry work as well as for cracking skulls.

CP14BaseShield.name: shield
CP14BaseShield.description: A wooden shield capable of withstanding multiple blows.

CP14BaseCrowbar.name: crowbar
CP14BaseCrowbar.description: A versatile and useful iron, for taking apart floors or other objects.

CP14BaseHoe.name: hoe
CP14BaseHoe.description: A gardening tool to prepare the soil for planting, or to clear weeds

CP14BaseMop.name: wooden mop
CP14BaseMop.description: Mop for cleaning floors from various unpleasant liquids

CP14BaseWrench.name: wrench
CP14BaseWrench.description: A common tool for assembly and disassembly. Remember: lefty latchy, righty removey.

CP14WallmountCrystalBase.name: sparkling quartz
CP14WallmountCrystalBase.description: bioluminescent quartz crystals that can take on any color - a very handy light source in a deep caves. Unfortunately, the luminous properties are very hard to preserve.

CP14WallmountFlagBase.name: tapestry
CP14WallmountFlagBase.description: A piece of cloth pinned to the wall.

CP14WallmauntGarlandBase.name: crystals garland
CP14WallmauntGarlandBase.description: Carefully crafted sparkling crystals tied on a string. For a festive attitude.

CP14IronDoor.name: iron door
CP14IronDoor.description: Well, if there's a solid iron door, there must be something valuable behind it.

CP14IronDoorWindowed.name: iron windowed door
CP14IronDoorWindowed.description: a solid iron door with a small window. You can look through it, of course, but it's hard to put your hand through.

CP14WoodenDoor.name: wooden door
CP14WoodenDoor.description: Not the most solid construction, but it's better than nothing.

CP14WoodenDoorWindowed.name: wooden windowed door
CP14WoodenDoorWindowed.description: Not the most solid construction, but it's better than nothing.

CP14FenceIronGrilleBase.name: iron grille
CP14FenceIronGrilleBase.description: A strong barrier made of iron bars welded together.

CP14FenceIronGrilleGate.name: iron grille gate
CP14FenceIronGrilleGate.description: Heavy iron gates in bars. Looks serious.

CP14FenceIronGrilleWindowBase.name: iron grille window
CP14FenceIronGrilleWindowBase.description: A strong barrier made of iron bars welded together. The absence of the bottom part allows you to slip objects through it.

CP14BaseFenceWood.name: wooden fence
CP14BaseFenceWood.description: A wooden fence. Don't plant splinters!

CP14FenceWoodGate.name: wooden fence gate
CP14FenceWoodGate.description: Big door in a big fence. For big people.

CP14BaseFenceWoodSmall.name: small wooden fence
CP14BaseFenceWoodSmall.description: A small wooden fence. It protects the area from unnecessary visitors who don't have a towel.

CP14FenceWoodSmallGate.name: small wooden fence gate
CP14FenceWoodSmallGate.description: Looking at this gate, a familiar image pops up in your head. Where's my piggy?

CP14GatherableWaterAirLily.name: air lily
CP14GatherableWaterAirLily.description: A light, delicate and airy flower. It is said that its special properties even allow it to breathe underwater...

CP14BaseBarrel.name: wooden barrel
CP14BaseBarrel.description: The simplest design for storing liquids.

CP14CraneBarrel.name: wooden crane barrel
CP14CraneBarrel.description: Large lying barrel with tap, for storing valuable liquids.

CP14CraneBarrelSmall.name: wooden small crane barrel
CP14CraneBarrelSmall.description: A small lying barrel with a tap to quickly pour liquid into mugs.

CP14BenchWood.name: wood bench
CP14BenchWood.description: A bench carved from wood, a comfortable part of the interior designed for sitting and relaxing.

CP14ChairWooden.name: wooden chair
CP14ChairWooden.description: Made of the most common planks. Simple and effective!

CP14Safe.name: safe
CP14Safe.description: A giant iron box for storing your most precious possessions. Extremely heavy and extremely strong.

CP14Mannequin.name: mannequin
CP14Mannequin.description: A handy stand for clothing or armour.

CP14TargetStake.name: target stake
CP14TargetStake.description: A wooden stand on which to fix a target for firing.

CP14TargetEffigy.name: target effigy
CP14TargetEffigy.description: The target is a scarecrow for practising close combat strikes.... or magic.

CP14WallmountLampEmpty.name: crystal wall lamp
CP14WallmountLampEmpty.description: A simple wallmount magical device that converts crystal energy into bright light.

CP14WallmountOrdersBorder.name: orders board
CP14WallmountOrdersBorder.description: Is there a job for a witcher?

CP14Workbench.name: workbench
CP14Workbench.description: Table for the production of various basic tools.

CP14WorkbenchCooking.name: cooking table
CP14WorkbenchCooking.description: A table to work with food. Time to cook!

CP14WorkbenchSewing.name: sewing table
CP14WorkbenchSewing.description: A table with embroidery tools to create different clothing and materials.

CP14FrameWooden.name: wooden wall frame
CP14FrameWooden.description: Wooden frame for any wooden wall.

CP14AlchemyNormalizer.name: solution normalizer
CP14AlchemyNormalizer.description: An alchemical device that removes fine precipitates from solutions, and stabilizes it for further work

CP14BaseVat.name: big vat
CP14BaseVat.description: A very large vat for storing huge amounts of liquid. Heavy, uncomfortable to carry.

CP14WorkbenchAnvil.name: anvil
CP14WorkbenchAnvil.description: A big piece of metal that allows you to turn square pieces of metal into pieces of metal in other, more useful shapes.

CP14WorkbenchFurnace.name: melting furnace
CP14WorkbenchFurnace.description: A red-hot stone construction that allows ores to be smelted into pure metal

CP14WoodenChest.name: wooden chest
CP14WoodenChest.description: A simple wooden chest for easy storage of junk.

CP14BrassChest.name: brass chest
CP14BrassChest.description: A simple brass chest for easy storage of junk.

CP14CrateCoffin.name: coffin
CP14CrateCoffin.description: A comfortable and nice looking coffin to comfortably await your resurrection.

CP14WallCardboard.name: cardboard Wall
CP14WallCardboard.description: A thin, flimsy wall made of paper and cardboard. Popular in warm countries.

CP14WindowWooden.name: wooden window
CP14WindowWooden.description: A wooden wall with a glass window in it.
